
# Auto Forward Bot

Features:
- Auto Forward Post to Multiple Source Channel to Multiple Destination Channel






## Environment Variables

To run this project, you will need to add the following environment variables on config.py file .

`API_ID` get from my.telegram.org

`API_HASH` get from my.telegram.org

`SESSION_STRING` Run generate_session_string.py file to generate session string 

`SOURCE_1` dd @miss_rose bot to your group. Forward message from your Private Channel to the group then type  /id to the forwarded message to get the PRIVATE_CHANNEL_ID. It will be something like -10054654654

`DESTINATION_1` add @miss_rose bot to your group. Forward message from your Private Channel to the group then type  /id to the forwarded message to get the PRIVATE_CHANNEL_ID. 










## Documentation

* Your account must be joined on source channel
* Your account must be admin of destination channel 




## Deployment
* Open terminal on Project folder and type
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt --no-cache
```


* Then Generate Session String 
```
python generate_session_string.py
```

To deploy this project locally
* Fill API_ID, API_HASH, SESSION_STRING, SOURCE_, DESTINATION_ on config.py



```bash
  python main.py
```

To Deploy on Heroku :
- create a repo on github
- upload this project
- create a heroku account
- connect github account to heroku
- then deploy the repo from heroku
- run the bot from resource tab on heroku


## If you need to add more source and more destination 
- add those variable on config.py
- add lines on main.py
- Check commented line on main.py and config.py file

